# Rust
target/
**/*.rs.bk
# Workspace policy: lib crate, do NOT commit the workspace lock file.
# v0.14 — anchored to the repo root (`/Cargo.lock`, not a bare `Cargo.lock`)
# so it does NOT also swallow `fuzz/Cargo.lock`: the cargo-fuzz binary
# workspace pins its lockfile for reproducible fuzzing, so that one IS
# committed (W0 codex finding).
/Cargo.lock

# v0.14 — cargo-fuzz derived output (build dir, grown corpus, crash repros).
# The committed surface is fuzz/Cargo.toml, fuzz/Cargo.lock,
# fuzz/fuzz_targets/, and the curated fuzz/seeds/.
fuzz/target/
fuzz/corpus/
fuzz/artifacts/

# Editor / OS
.idea/
.vscode/
.DS_Store
*.swp

